		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I wonder what kind of low pass filters did televisions use.  These are the kinds of LPF I know.<br /><br />sinc: perfect roll-off, but far too expensive to implement<br />boxcar: Weak roll-off<br />gaussian: Weak roll-off<br />RC: Easiest to implement in analog hardware, but has the weakest roll-off

		

		</td>
	</tr>
